SegmentationTrainer.fit() loop:
After each epoch (after logging metrics and saving best-metric checkpoints):
1. Write epoch_latest.yaml to checkpoint_dir / "epoch_latest.yaml":
    epoch: {epoch_number}
    fold: {fold_id}
    mlflow_run_id: {tracker.run_id}
    best_val_loss: {best_val_loss}
    timestamp: {datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()}
2. Save epoch_latest.pth (model state_dict only, not optimizer state):
    torch.save(model.state_dict(), checkpoint_dir / "epoch_latest.pth")
3. SIGTERM handler: on receipt, write epoch_latest.yaml and epoch_latest.pth then sys.exit(0)

Uses yaml.dump() for writing (NOT f-string or string concatenation).
Uses yaml.safe_load() for reading in check_resume_state_task().
NO regex for reading epoch_latest.yaml.

@task(name="dvc-pull") def dvc_pull_task(data_dir: Path, dvc_rev: str | None = None, remote: str | None = None) -> str: """Pull DVC-tracked data at optional revision. Returns: git commit hash of the DVC revision pulled. """ import subprocess cmd = ["dvc", "pull"] if dvc_rev: cmd.extend(["--rev", dvc_rev]) if remote: cmd.extend(["--remote", remote]) result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, cwd=data_dir, check=True) # Get current DVC commit: use subprocess.run(["git", "rev-parse", "HEAD"]) rev_result = subprocess.run( ["git", "rev-parse", "HEAD"], capture_output=True, text=True, cwd=data_dir, check=True ) return rev_result.stdout.strip()
run_data_flow() accepts dvc_rev and dvc_remote parameters. Logs data_dvc_commit param to MLflow.
configs/dvc/remotes.yaml defines local, s3, gcs, azure, hetzner remotes. DVC_REMOTE env var selects the active remote.
